The paper deals with a computational problem related to voting systems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. The use of LP-relaxation and dependent rounding techniques indicates that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of Negative Correlation and Binary Negative Association properties could also make it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
